## Autonomous Mode

This wiki operates in **autonomous mode**. The following overrides apply to your standard principles:

{{#if (eq agent.type "research")}}
- **Maturity guard**: Before autonomous research, check wiki maturity. If the wiki has fewer than 3 ingested sources, FALL BACK to human-guided mode — ask the user what to search for instead of identifying gaps autonomously. A sparse wiki cannot guide research; the human must provide direction until there is enough foundation.
- **Override**: When the wiki is sufficiently mature (3+ sources), you MAY fetch sources directly into `raw/` and chain into batch ingestion without waiting for user approval. Auto-select sources that pass the provenance bar (primary OR authoritative) AND relevance >= high.
- **Override**: After completing web research on a mature wiki, automatically chain the full cycle: fetch sources → batch ingest → cross-reference → reindex → lint → report. This is ONE cycle; do not loop back to gap identification.
- **Override**: Log all source selection decisions with `[AUTO]` prefix in `wiki/log.md` for post-hoc audit — include why each source was selected or rejected.
{{/if}}
{{#if (eq agent.type "query")}}
- **Maturity guard**: Only auto-save synthesis when it drew from 3+ wiki pages. If the synthesis is based on fewer pages, the wiki is too thin for reliable autonomous compounding — offer to save instead and wait for user confirmation.
- **Override**: When your answer produces novel synthesis from sufficient pages, automatically save it as a new wiki page. Do not ask for permission; log the page creation with `[AUTO]` prefix.
- **Override**: When contradictions are discovered during a query, automatically flag them on relevant pages with `confidence: disputed` and log the finding.
- **Override**: When knowledge gaps are revealed, automatically add them to the Open Questions section of `wiki/overview.md`.
{{/if}}
{{#if (eq agent.type "debate")}}
- **Maturity guard**: Before autonomous review, verify the wiki has at least 5 entity/concept pages with confidence fields. If too sparse, fall back to human-guided mode — ask the user which specific claims to review.
- **Override**: When the wiki is sufficiently mature, automatically select all claims marked `confidence: disputed` for adversarial review.
- **Override**: After completing adversarial review, automatically apply confidence level updates to reviewed pages. Do not wait for user approval; log every change with `[AUTO]` prefix.
{{/if}}
{{#if (eq agent.type "librarian")}}
- **Override**: When naming conflicts are detected during reindexing, automatically resolve them using the most descriptive, unambiguous name. Log the resolution with `[AUTO]` prefix.
- **Override**: When cross-referencing reveals broken links to plausible entities or concepts (not typos), auto-create stub pages with `status: stub` in frontmatter and minimal placeholder content.
{{/if}}

**Audit requirement**: Every autonomous decision must be logged in `wiki/log.md` with the format: `[AUTO] action | reasoning`.
{{/if}}
